@mikengine: I had to install `AutoMapper 2.2.1`.

You could try the patch to the .NET Framework 4 too: 

http://support.microsoft.com/kb/2468871

@leniel : Thanks a lot!

It's some complex try with the patch of .net. I don't have control of production server. =/

I revert back to 2.2.1 version and now works. For now it's ok.

We're seeing something similar.  I'm wondering if the PCL piece has a bug in it because I'm able to repro with the following in VS 2012:
1. Create a new .NET 4.5 class library
2. Add in the AutoMapper (latest release or pre-release) and CuttingEdge.Conditions (can really be any library without PCL hooks by the looks of it) Nuget packages
3. Create an AutoMapper Mapping Profile such as

   public class TestProfile : Profile
   {
       protected override void Configure()
       {
           CreateMap<string, string>();
       }
   }
4. Build
5. Attempt to resolve types in the file using something like PowerShell:

   $x = [Reflection.Assembly]::LoadFile("C:\Projects\ClassLibrary1\bin\debug\ClassLibrary1.dll")
   $x.GetType()

You will get a TypeLoadException and if you inspect into the LoaderExceptions collection you will see that the runtime is having an issue resolving System.Core and is looking for 2.0.5.0.
